<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910531-0128</DOCNO><DOCID>910531-0128.</DOCID><HL>   Litton Gets Soviet Auto Award</HL><DATE>05/31/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17</SO><CO>   LIT</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AUTOMOBILES (AUT)DIVERSIFIED TECHNOLOGY (DTC)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)CANADA (CN)SOVIET UNION (UR)</RE><LP>   BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. -- Litton Industries Inc. said itwas awarded a $45 million contract by Soviet auto maker VolgaAuto Works to provide two machining systems to produce enginecomponents at the company's main Togliatti, U.S.S.R. plant.   Litton, a defense and marine systems company, saidinstallation of the systems is scheduled to begin by mid-1992and be completed by the end of the year.</LP><TEXT>   Financing will come from Canadian Export DevelopmentCorp., a government-owned concern that provides export creditand other financial services.</TEXT></DOC>